<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-513-192  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 513 192.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  May 28 1990 v7 n22 p45(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Appeals Court ruling has far-reaching implications. (controversycontinues over Judge Harold Greene's Modified Final Judgement)(column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pearce, Alan.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A Washington DC Circuit Court of Appeals formally questioned USDistrict Court Judge Harold Greene's restrictions on the regionalBell holding companies (RBHCs) regarding the offering ofinformation services, in Apr 1990.andP;  As a result Greene may beforced to review the limitations imposed upon the RBHCs by theModified Final Judgement, taking into consideration only antitrustissues.andP;  MCI Communications Corp is spearheading a group ofcompanies asking for a stay of the Appeal Court's mandate untilthe case can be appealed to the US Supreme Court.andP;  The SupremeCourt will not decide whether or not to hear the case until theFall.andP;  It appears as through the Modified Final Judgement may befading away, which is good news for the RBHCs as well as forusers, who stand to benefit by greater competition and establishedtariffed rates.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Legal IssuesUnited States. Court of Appeals for the District of ColumbiaCircuitBell Regional Holding CompaniesGovernment RegulationTelecommunications.andO;Person:    Greene, Harold (cases).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>